# Security rules — Meavo org standard

Org standard (see STANDARDS.md §4 in meavo-agent-templates). Deviations for this repo are listed at the bottom.

## Auth at every layer

- Verify auth independently in: middleware (pages), section layouts, Server Actions, and API routes.
- Middleware passes `/api/*` through — never assume an API route is protected.
- This repo's auth gate: `getTasksUser()` / `requireTasksUser()` in `src/lib/access.ts`; the `(app)` layout (`src/app/(app)/layout.tsx`) and every Server Action call it independently.
- Tool card gating: check `ToolCardAccess` for `TASKS_TOOL_CARD_ID` (default `seed-tasks-tool`, via `TASKS_CARD_ID` in `src/lib/tasks-config.ts`) at login AND on every authenticated request, so revocation in gateway Admin takes effect immediately. Never look up the card by `linkedAppKey` at runtime.
- Per-board/task authorization on top of the app gate: `requireWorkspaceView/Edit`, `requireTaskEdit` in `src/lib/domain/task-authz.ts`.

## Sessions & credentials

- NextAuth v5 JWT sessions; `systemRole` refreshed from DB in the JWT/session callbacks (`src/lib/auth.ts`, types in `src/types/next-auth.d.ts`).
- Passwords: bcryptjs 12 rounds (`src/lib/password.ts`). Login throttling via shared `LoginThrottle` table (`src/lib/login-throttle.ts`).
- Google OAuth is invite-only — user must already exist in the DB and hold the Tasks tool card (`src/lib/google-auth.ts`).

## Routes & rendering

- Cron routes: `CRON_SECRET` Bearer auth via `isAuthorizedCronRequest()` (`src/lib/cron-auth.ts`) on every `/api/cron/*` handler.
- `export const dynamic = "force-dynamic"` on authenticated layouts and DB-touching pages.
- Never return stack traces to clients in production.

## Headers & content

- `next.config.ts` sets: `X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff`, `X-Frame-Options: DENY`, `Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin`, `Strict-Transport-Security`.
- No file uploads in this app today — if adding any, follow the org standard (Vercel Blob, 10 MB, MIME + extension validation, authenticated download route).

## Secrets

- No secrets in client code, comments, or committed files.
- User-supplied Slack webhook URLs must start with `https://hooks.slack.com/` (validated in `src/app/actions/settings.ts`).
- Document env var names only, never values.

## Repo-specific deviations

- **Admin bypass:** users with `systemRole === "ADMIN"` skip the tool-card check (`src/lib/access.ts`) and get owner-level access to every workspace (`src/lib/domain/task-authz.ts`). STANDARDS.md §8 prefers explicit seeded access for admins — keep the existing behaviour unless asked to change it.
- **`X-Frame-Options: DENY`** (stricter than the org's `SAMEORIGIN`).
- **No `.env.example` committed** — `.gitignore` ignores `.env*`; env var names are documented in `README.md` and `docs/architecture.md`.
